## Polymorphic Associations

One model belongs to multiple other models.

```ruby
# Create polymorphic table
create_table :comments do |t|
  # Polymorphic association
  t.references :commentable, polymorphic: true, null: false
  # Creates: commentable_id and commentable_type
  
  t.references :user, null: false, foreign_key: true
  t.text :body, null: false
  
  t.timestamps
end

add_index :comments, [:commentable_type, :commentable_id]
```

```ruby
# Models
class Comment < ApplicationRecord
  belongs_to :commentable, polymorphic: true
  belongs_to :user
end

class Article < ApplicationRecord
  has_many :comments, as: :commentable
end

class Video < ApplicationRecord
  has_many :comments, as: :commentable
end

# Usage
article.comments.create(user: user, body: "Great article!")
video.comments.create(user: user, body: "Nice video!")
```

